  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Adler Spa Resort Dolomiti is luxurious in every sense of the word. Everyone here will go out of their way to make sure you have the most enjoyable stay possible. The spa is out of this world. </p>
<h2>Easy access to Dolomite activities</h2>
<p>This is the place to be if you want to get out and explore the <a data-udi="umb://document/f7e065ba2a3d40d7893ad1b116880496" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f7e065ba2a3d40d7893ad1b116880496}" title="The Dolomites">Dolomites</a>. You’ve got access to the hotel’s e-bikes for free so grab one and set off up the mountain. You could also join a free guided tour with an e-bike from Monday to Saturday. You’ll be with an experienced guide and get to see some of the best trails in the area. There are guided hikes too, which run every day except Sunday, and Nordic hikes a couple of times a week. If you’re travelling with your family, the kids club is great. It's run by experienced staff and has plenty to keep children entertained all day. It’s free to use but you might need to pre-book.</p>
<h2>Explore Ortisei, right on the doorstep </h2>
<p>We love exploring the village of <a data-udi="umb://document/a7a8ad5233804c39b1e02e8dd02cc1fc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a7a8ad5233804c39b1e02e8dd02cc1fc}" title="Ortisei">Ortisei</a>, it’s got a real alpine charm about it. The hotel’s right in the centre so head out for a quick walk before dinner if you can. It might be hard to tear yourself away from the hotel though – the gardens are incredibly relaxing with lots of space to spread out and fantastic views. Lots of people head to the hotel just for its spa and it’s not hard to see why. We challenge anyone to come away from here and not feel like a brand new person.</p>]]></description>
