  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Superior Rooms</strong> sleep up to three people and offer a cosy space finished in warm colours and a mix of traditional and modern furnishings. Rooms have a bathroom with shower, and also have a balcony. </p>
<p><strong>Superior Single Rooms </strong>are a great choice for solo travellers. They have a bath with an overhead shower. </p>
<p><strong>Family Suites</strong> can sleep up to four people and offer plenty of space for the whole family. They have a double bedroom which leads through to the second bedroom with twin beds. Rooms are available on request, please call to book.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Tea &amp; Coffee making facilities</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Safe</li>
</ul>
<p>Cots are available on request for approx. €40 per day, payable locally. </p>
<p><strong>Local fees &amp; taxes</strong></p>
<p>Resort tourist tax of approx. €3.90 per person per day is payable locally (not applicable to children under 13 years old).</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
